info.title: RESTful API Car Management
info.description:
# üöÄ Get started with the API Collection

This collection provides you with CRUD operations for users, cars, and authentication routes, including examples of JWT authentication for protected endpoints.

## üîñ **How to use this collection**

### **Step 1: Set up the Base URL**

A variable named `base_url` is included to help you manage your API's base URL. Currently, it is set to `http://localhost:3000/api/v1`. Update it if your API base URL changes.

### **Step 2: Send Requests**

Perform CRUD operations on users and cars, as well as authentication requests, using the POST, GET, PATCH, and DELETE HTTP methods. Each request example includes a sample Body payload or JWT authentication setup as required.

### **Step 3: View Responses**

Observe the response tab to confirm the status code (e.g., 200 OK, 404 Not Found), response time, and size.

### **Step 4: Send Body Data**

To create or update users and cars, modify the Body data in the request.

Example JSON payload:

```
{
    "name": "Wahyu",
    "age": 20,
    "address": "Kosan sebelah Amikom",
    "email": "wahyuabc@mail.com",
    "password": "passwordddd"
}
```

### **Step 5: Update and Use Variables**

The `base_url` variable can be used in each request URL. For authenticated requests, ensure you add your JWT token as a `Bearer` token in the Authorization tab.

### **Step 6: Add Tests in the "Tests" Tab**

Postman allows you to run JavaScript tests to validate API responses, such as verifying status codes and checking JSON structures.

## üìò Endpoints Overview

### **Authentication**
- `POST {{base_url}}/auth/login` ‚Äì User login
- `POST {{base_url}}/auth/register` ‚Äì User registration

### **Users**
- `GET {{base_url}}/users` ‚Äì Retrieve all users (requires JWT)
- `GET {{base_url}}/users/:id` ‚Äì Retrieve a user by ID (requires JWT)
- `GET {{base_url}}/users/current-user` ‚Äì Retrieve current user by ID (requires JWT) 
- `PATCH {{base_url}}/users/:id` ‚Äì Update a user (requires JWT)
- `DELETE {{base_url}}/users/:id` ‚Äì Delete a user (requires JWT)
- `POST {{base_url}}/users/` ‚Äì Create an admin user (requires JWT)

### **Cars**
- `GET {{base_url}}/cars` ‚Äì Retrieve all cars 
- `POST {{base_url}}/cars` ‚Äì Add a new car (requires JWT)
- `DELETE {{base_url}}/cars/:id` ‚Äì Delete a car (requires JWT)
- `PATCH {{base_url}}/cars/:id` ‚Äì Update a car (requires JWT)
- `GET {{base_url}}/cars/soft-deleted` ‚Äì Retrieve deleted cars (requires JWT)
- `GET {{base_url}}/cars/:id` ‚Äì Retrieve a car by ID

- [Using variables](https://learning.postman.com/docs/sending-requests/variables/)
- [Writing scripts](https://learning.postman.com/docs/writing-scripts/intro-to-scripts/)
